(178, 1, '2015-01-25 15:03:37', '2015-01-25 15:03:37', '[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text css_animation=""]\n<h3>Support Services Technician– Ottawa</h3>\nKanatek has been in business for over 30 years and we have built our reputation on trust, quality, and our expertise in the IT field.   We are an evolving company, driven by a commitment to our clients.  Over the years, our company has attracted and maintained top level talent and has supported and encouraged those people to be the best in the industry. Our success is a testament to these people.  Our offices are located in Ottawa (headquarters) and Toronto.\n\nKanatek requires a knowledgeable Technical Support Administrator to troubleshoot technical problems, providing technical advice, product upgrade and installation support to our clients. Our clients range in size from middle to very large companies and government agencies; therefore if you enjoy a fast paced environment and supporting leading edge technology this is the role for you.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h5>Main responsibilities</h5>\n<ul>\n	<li>To provide technical support both remotely and on site for our Enterprise customers; determine the nature and likely causes of the problem, thus recommending corrective action and guiding the customer through the necessary steps to solve the issue</li>\n	<li>Assist Symantec customers in resolving technical issues with Symantec products including, NetBackup, Volume Manager, File System, Cluster Server, Enterprise Vault, etc.</li>\n	<li>Assist Quantum customers in logging and managing HW/SW cases for Quantum tape libraries</li>\n	<li>Escalate urgent issues to vendors and be a liaison between vendors and customers</li>\n	<li>Interact with the Sales team to discuss client accounts</li>\n	<li>Provide, from time to time, on-site delivery and installation of the Kanatek product portfolio</li>\n	<li>Provide consulting, design, and/or implementation support for data storage and protection</li>\n	<li>Provide technical services including assessments, analysis, installation and support for clients  in a highly complex data storage environment</li>\n	<li>Work closely with sales, technical services and support groups, external vendor partners, and the customer to ensure a smooth implementation and transition</li>\n	<li>Develop installation documentation and operation procedures</li>\n	<li>Implement solutions in accordance with Kanatek standards and as per Statement of Work</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n<h5>Additional Responsibilities</h5>\n<ul>\n	<li>Must maintain a thorough understanding of product applications that Kanatek resells, as well as complete all documentation relating to tracking problem resolutions for calls received in Kanatek’s Client Services Database</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n<h5>Requirements</h5>\n<ul>\n	<li>Recent post-secondary graduate</li>\n	<li>Experience servicing and working with the wide array of Symantec products is beneficial; specifically Enterprise Vault</li>\n	<li>Solid understanding of networking and skills in troubleshooting/identifying network issues</li>\n	<li>Strong UNIX and/or Windows Operating Systems administration skills</li>\n	<li>Willing to travel to different client locations</li>\n	<li>Available to be on-call for support on rotation</li>\n	<li>Ability to work in a high pressure environment</li>\n	<li>Available to work evenings or weekends on occasion</li>\n</ul>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text css_animation=""]\n\nIf you are interested in the position, please email us at <a href="mailto:hr@kanatek.com">hr@kanatek.com</a> or fill out the form below.\n\n[/vc_column_text][contact-form-7 id="172" title="Job Application"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Career - Support Services Technician', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '167-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-01-25 15:03:37', '2015-01-25 15:03:37', '', 167, 'http://localhost/kanatek/2015/01/25/167-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
